:Entry: get_definition_: 02/02/84  get_definition_


Function: returns a pointer to a specified definition within an object
segment.


Syntax:
declare get_definition_ entry (ptr, char(*), char(*), ptr,
     fixed bin(35));
call get_definition_ (def_section_ptr, segname, entryname, def_ptr,
     code);


Arguments:
def_section_ptr
   is a pointer to the definition section of the object segment.  This
   pointer can be obtained via the object_info_ subroutine.  (Input)
segname
   is the name of the object segment.  (Input)
entryname
   is the name of the desired entry point.  (Input)
def_ptr
   is a pointer to the definition for the entry point.  (Output)
code
   is a standard status code.  If the entry point is found, code is 0.
   (Output)
